reviewText: Even though I am thinking about getting the uncut version of the first and second season, I still want to keep this. I don't plan on getting rid of my Sailor Moon stuff.This movie is really important to get. And get this one before you get Love conquers all!". If you don't you'll get confused.First episode:A monster corrupts Amy's friends and makes them think that Amy cheats on her exams.Second episode:A monster makes the kids at Rini's school act evil.Third episode:When the scouts travel to the future to help Rini, the Genie of the Timewarp spilts them up in the timewarp that goes to the future.Fourth episode:If you're a new Sailor Moon fan, this is just one of the reasons why you should buy this.Fifth episode:Since Emerald is jealous of Prince Diamond being obsessed with Sailor Moon, she wants to be the queen and have Prince Diamond rule by her side, but ends up turning into a dragon.

reviewText: I know people will argue but not other season of Sailor Moon is better. Yes I think this season is even better than Moon-S-SuperS-and the last season Stars. All season are great but this has the best story line. S-SuperS-and Stars are all the same except for different bad guys and a different ending. In S-SuperS-and Stars the bad guy is doing the same thing: looking for pure heart crystals, dream mirrors, or star seeds. It's the same thing every episode. Bad guy attacks person their crystal/mirror/or star seed appear and then the bad guy realizes its not the one they are looking for and then Sailor Moon kills them and the next episode is just the same. Don't get me wrong, I love all the seasons but everyone has to admit that is what happens in almost every episode until the end.Sailor Moon R leaves you with a curious feeling. And even though I'd seen all of the seasons before I saw R I was still liking the mystery of Rini's parents (even though we know who they are). The season just gets great by this tape because the scouts go to the future and many secrets are revealed. One secret is why everyone is still alive 1,000 yrs later. Plus I think one of the episodes is great (probably a lot better in the true uncut japanese version and not like the Pioneer version on DVD that they say is uncut) but I don't think little kids would like it, and they shouldn't since the show in japan was made for teenagers.Anyway this tape is an awesome tape. You even finally get to meet Sailor Pluto in true form.
